.TH "BTRFS\-FILE\-HISTORY" "8" "" "btrfs\-file\-history" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
btrfs\-file\-history \[em] visualize file and directory lifecycle across
btrfs snapshots
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]btrfs\-file\-history\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] \f[B]tree\f[R]
\f[I]MOUNT_POINT\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]btrfs\-file\-history\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] \f[B]history\f[R]
\f[I]MOUNT_POINT\f[R] \f[I]FILE_PATH\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]btrfs\-file\-history\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] \f[B]diff\f[R]
\f[I]MOUNT_POINT\f[R] \f[I]FILE_PATH\f[R] \f[I]SNAP_OLD\f[R]
\f[I]SNAP_NEW\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]btrfs\-file\-history\f[R] tracks how files and directories change
across btrfs snapshots.
It can display the full subvolume tree, show a file\[cq]s history
timeline (creation, modifications, deletions), and diff a file between
two specific snapshots.
.PP
File state detection uses size, mtime, optional checksums, and shared
extent analysis to distinguish actual content changes from
metadata\-only updates.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\f[B]tree\f[R] \f[I]MOUNT_POINT\f[R]
Show the btrfs subvolume tree.
\f[I]MOUNT_POINT\f[R] is the filesystem root.
Use \f[B]\-\-format\f[R] to output as text (default), Graphviz DOT, or
JSON.
.TP
\f[B]history\f[R] \f[I]MOUNT_POINT\f[R] \f[I]FILE_PATH\f[R]
Show file history across all snapshots.
\f[I]FILE_PATH\f[R] can be absolute (e.g.\ \f[CR]/home/user/file\f[R])
or relative to the subvolume root.
Use \f[B]\-\-checksum\f[R] for content\-based change detection.
Use \f[B]\-\-extents\f[R] to analyze shared physical extents.
Use \f[B]\-\-du\f[R] to compute shared/exclusive bytes.
Use \f[B]\-\-no\-tree\f[R] to suppress the subvolume tree output.
Use \f[B]\-\-filter\f[R] \f[I]PATTERN\f[R] to limit scanning to specific
subvolumes.
.TP
\f[B]diff\f[R] \f[I]MOUNT_POINT\f[R] \f[I]FILE_PATH\f[R] \f[I]SNAP_OLD\f[R] \f[I]SNAP_NEW\f[R]
Diff a file between two snapshots.
Prints size delta, content equality, shared extent count, and text diff.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-\-no\-color\f[R]
Disable colored output.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-format\f[R] \f[I]FORMAT\f[R]
Output format for \f[B]tree\f[R] and \f[B]history\f[R]: \f[CR]text\f[R]
(default), \f[CR]dot\f[R], or \f[CR]json\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-\-checksum\f[R]
Compute checksums for accurate change detection (\f[B]history\f[R]
only).
.TP
\f[B]\-\-extents\f[R]
Analyze shared physical extents via filefrag (\f[B]history\f[R] only).
.TP
\f[B]\-\-du\f[R]
Compute shared/exclusive bytes via btrfs du (\f[B]history\f[R] only).
.TP
\f[B]\-\-no\-tree\f[R]
Don\[cq]t show subvolume tree, only the timeline (\f[B]history\f[R]
only).
.TP
\f[B]\-\-filter\f[R] \f[I]PATTERN\f[R] [\f[I]PATTERN\f[R]\&...]
Only scan subvolumes matching the given pattern(s) (\f[B]history\f[R]
only).
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\-\-help\f[R]
Show usage summary and exit.
.TP
\f[B]\-V\f[R], \f[B]\-\-version\f[R]
Print version and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Success.
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
Error.
Common causes: not a btrfs filesystem, path not found, permission
denied, invalid snapshot references.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[B]\[ti]/.local/state/btrfs\-file\-history/*\f[R]
State files.
